          </trait>
          <floruit from="1680" to="1680">fl. 1680</floruit>
          <affiliation key="l_15" role="Performed a grand-scale yajña in 1698 in Svāmimalai, evidenced in the Ācāraṇavanitā by Appādhvarin.">
            <placeName>Svamimalai</placeName>
          </affiliation>
          <note>He was the mantrin of Śāhaji I of Thanjavur. </note>
          <note>Much of the earlier patronage of scholars by Śāhaji I flowed through Tryambakarāyamakhin’s hands (Raghavan, Intro to Śāhendravilāsa, p.27)</note>
        </person>
